The South African Savings Institute says there's an urgent need to equip young people with savings skills. JOHANNESBURG - July is savings month and this year the campaign is focused on the youth. The South African Savings Institute says there's an urgent need to equip young people with savings skills. READ: 'Respect brown and silver coins': Savings Institute Young people have embraced the culture of credit, making it difficult for them to save, according to the institute. They are advising people to save by any means necessary, even by counting small change.